[00:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] &gt;&gt; This is the Martin Mac Aura remote follow [music] spot solution. Controlling one or multiple fixtures with the smoothest and most accurate control. Offering top notch results when combined [music] with Martin\'s latest performance'

[00:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'moving heads, but compatible with any fixture [music] from any brand. The Mac Aura system is built around [music] a high resolution fluid head encoder, which relays the operator\'s movements with precise and ergonomic'

[00:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'operation. [music] It controls one or multiple fixtures, allowing you to freely mix fixture [music] models and brands as you like. One or multiple of those fixtures is then fitted [music] with a camera, and'

[00:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can dynamically change between those cameras during operation. The Mac Aura system can take full control of your lighting fixtures without [music] needing a lighting console. But, you can also merge controls from a lighting console [music] inside the Mac'

[00:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Aura system and only hand over part of the controls to the follow spot operator. The built-in [music] screen, programmable faders, and LCD buttons make the Mac Aura system extremely easy [music] to set up and operate.'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Let\'s explore some of the elements [music] which make Martin Mac Aura such a unique and brand agnostic remote follow spot solution. Mac Aura [music] combines the reliability and natural'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'operation of a manual follow spot with the safety and ergonomics of modern technology. The system can be set up in a matter of minutes [music] without an extensive calibration procedure, and it integrates'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'nicely into any standard lighting network. The intuitive controls will make any operator feel at home &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; right away without a complex training. Whether you\'re working in concerts and touring, theater or broadcast, corporate'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'events or sporting [music] events, Martin Mac Aura will fit right in. The fluid head encoder relays [music] the operator\'s movements with precision and the most natural feeling available.'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'While the [music] large touchscreen provides the operator with a clear overview of the stage with real-time information and controls [music] being overlaid. The ergonomic handles include faders which can be assigned [music] to any'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'parameter on the fly. Dimmer, focus, zoom, iris, you decide which parameter you want at your fingertips. The handles also include rollers to access parameters such as [music] the Z axis height of your artist.'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The right handle includes 15 LCD buttons which can be programmed with presets for easy recall. Position presets [music] for pickup points, color presets, or Z axis presets to compensate for various'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stage [music] heights. Any combination is possible here. The follow spot operator sees the stage through a camera [music] attached to lighting fixture. The camera feed is simply sent over a standard network removing the need for'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dedicated video [music] cables. You can even equip multiple fixtures with a camera and change your point of view on [music] the fly without any interruption to the operation of the system. Great [music] for 360° application.'

[02:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In environments with multiple follow spot operators, &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; you can easily hand over cameras and fixtures between the operators at any given time. [music] The Macula system can control one or multiple fixtures fully independently'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'without needing a [music] lighting console. Simply patch the fixtures in the Macula system, any fixture from any brand on any dynamic switch universe, &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; and you take full control from the system.'

[03:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The faders are freely assignable &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; to any parameter. For quick recall of specific parameters or entire looks, you can create presets [music] and then assign these to the LCD buttons for easy recall. The built-in bank system allows you to'

[03:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control which fixtures you\'re controlling at any [music] given time. One single fixture following the artist for one song and then 12 more fixtures following along on the next [music] song. With Macula, you can change this'

[03:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on the fly. Controls from a lighting console can also [music] be merged inside Macula and then sent forwards to the lighting fixtures. So, you can freely [music] decide what parameters to control here on Macula and'

[03:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which fixture parameters to control from the lighting desk. You simply activate or deactivate [music] presets as needed. Or even combine the dimmer from the lighting console with the dimmer on the Macula system.'

[04:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'For more advanced workflows, [music] Macula also supports the PosistageNet or PSN protocol towards a lighting console or software, which will then use the 3D coordinates that are calculated and sent'

[04:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] out from Macula. So, there you have it. The Martin Macula remote follow spot system. Offering the smoothest and most [music] accurate fixture movements. Controlling one or multiple fixtures'

[04:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'while allowing you to freely mix different models and [music] brands as you like. Easy to set up using standard networking infrastructure and allowing you to freely mix controls from a lighting console as needed.'

[04:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] Whether you\'re controlling a single follow spot or a complex system with many fixtures tracking along, Martin Macula can do it all.'
